					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">A few years ago RushJet1 made a DPCM tool:<br /><a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6975" class="postlink">http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6975</a><br /><br />One of the options it has is just an easy way to experiment with different amounts of pre-gain to try and find a good balance between clipping and quantization.<br /><br />I think a more ideal tool would have maybe a well formed EQ and not just gain (and probably a more advanced sample encoder), but I don't think anyone's really made the perfect DMC tool yet.<br /><br />lidnariq: that looks pretty neat. For a long time I've had a &quot;convert FFT to best-fit NES APU registers at 60hz&quot; note on my to do list, so it's pretty cool to see someone actually has done it, at least for noise. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

